  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, WSe 2 exhibits exceptional nonlinear optical response, which can be exploited to realize nonlinear transistors.",
    "Tong et al.",
    "achieved this by integrating WSe 2 with lithium niobite, realizing nonlinear transistors and non-volatile memory with memory operating functionality [101].",
    "Additionally, Sebastian et al.",
    "utilized WSe 2 memtransistors integrated with circuits to implement the hyperbolic tangent and sigmoid activation functions in an artificial neuron [102].Tin sulfide (SnS) is a layered semiconductor with remarkable optical sensitivity, characterized by abundant defect states originating from both Sn and S vacancies, many of which are located within the bandgap."
  ],
